Focus
- Single-target geometric resonance factorization ONLY.
- Target N = 137524771864208156028430259349934309717.
- Goal: find p and q such that p*q == N using PURE GEOMETRIC RESONANCE (no classical fallbacks).

Operating mode
- Geometric-only: Dirichlet kernel sharpening + k-grid sweep + fractional comb around m0 = round(k*ln N / 2π) + intersection filtering.
- BANNED unless explicitly requested: ECM, Pollard’s Rho, QS/SIQS, NFS, sieves, random restarts that are not resonance-driven.
- Deterministic runs with explicit precision and seeds; zero network; minimal dependencies.

Repro & calibration (defaults — override per run as needed)
- mp.dps = 512
- k-range: center ~0.30, ±10% window (0.27–0.33) unless specified
- Dirichlet order J = 6 (try 8 only if requested)
- comb_range = 80–100; fine step ≤ 1e-4
- samples = 1500 (calibration), thresholds: amplitude ≥ 0.98 (tighten only when asked)
- CPU/threads guard: confirm if > 5 minutes expected or > 8 threads requested
- RNG: seed all sources and echo seeds in output

Outputs & artifacts
- STDOUT: minimal.
  - Always print parameters first (N, k-range, J, mp.dps, seeds).
  - On success print ONLY: p, q, and “verified: p*q==N” (with the literal N shown).
- Logs → ./runs/
- JSON/CSV summaries → ./results/ (include filename prefix N-137524771864208156028430259349934309717-yyyy-mm-ddThhmmss)

Validation checklist (ALWAYS)
1) Echo N exactly: 137524771864208156028430259349934309717
2) Show params (mp.dps, k-range, J, samples, m-span, thresholds, seeds).
3) On hit: print p, q, and assert p*q==N; show the full equality line p*q==137524771864208156028430259349934309717.
4) Save config + summary metrics to ./results/; keep raw logs in ./runs/.
5) No claims of success without the equality line.

Commands (use these templates)
- Python (example):
  python3 python/demo_z5d_rsa.py 137524771864208156028430259349934309717 --dps 512 --samples 1500 --m-span 80 --J 6 --threshold 0.98 --k-lo 0.27 --k-hi 0.33 --bias 0 --out ./results/

- Gradle (example):
  ./gradlew run --args="137524771864208156028430259349934309717 --mc-digits=260 --samples=1500 --m-span=80 --J=6 --threshold=0.98 --k-lo=0.27 --k-hi=0.33 --bias=0" \    -Djava.util.concurrent.ForkJoinPool.common.parallelism=8

House rules
- No edits outside targeted files; when editing code, provide exact patch/diff.
- No dependency upgrades unless explicitly requested.
- Keep code changes surgical and reversible; prefer flags over rewrites.
- Prefer stdlib + mpmath/numpy for Python; minimal Gradle deps for Java.

